main event: An observer reported seeing a bright, circular light in the sky with a flashing strobe-like effect in September 1966.
interesting points: The light was observed for about 20 seconds before disappearing., The observer noted that the object appeared to have a blue-grey reflective color., The object was described as saucer-shaped and about the size of a US silver dollar., It was estimated to be moving at a speed of 2-3,000 mph., No photograph of the incident was available, but there was a hand-drawn sketch included.
witness description: The observer filled out a questionnaire detailing their sighting.
